      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "UBIQUITOUS (3) put in a much better performance last start when in the placings at Bendigo behind Over Achiever (23.90) in a Grade 5. Has the early speed to give a sight. One of the leading chances. AUSSIE WAGYU (7) was never in contention last time after settling well back at Ballarat, but prior to that won by 1.1 lengths at this track (22.72) beating Did So in a Grade 5 on March 27. The form from his last run is stacking up nicely. Expected to feature in the finish. OUT OF ELITE (2) turned in a fair run last time from the squeeze finishing fourth by 4 lengths (22.79). Has ability and is one of the better chances. ULTIMO (1) should bounce back after an unplaced effort here recently.",
